 Sylvester Idowu in Warri The Founding Leader and 2015 Governorship Candidate of All Progressives Congress (APC) in Delta State, Mr. O’tega Emerhor, has said that the emergence of Senator Bola Ahmed Tinubu, as the presidential candidate of the party would record resounding victory for APC in 2023 general elections. Emerhor, in a statement he personally signed yesterday, described Tinubu’s victory as well deserved, and commended him for his hard work, perseverance, doggedness and sagacity. He said: “The victory came against all odds and in the face of very strong and determined opponents.” Emerhor further declared him as the man of these times adding “Nigeria is currently at a crossroad. He said: “Our President Muhammadu Buhari having lifted Nigeria from the hole  that PDP dug the country into, and with the country still beset with hydra-headed issues ranging from the economy to insecurity to infrastructure deficit and even the unity of the country, Tinubu is indeed the Man of these Times. “The man who can sustain and escalate the progression of success recorded so far. A man who has done it before in Lagos State, can do it again for Nigeria,” he said. He described Tinubu as “a man of capacity, a visionary extraordinary. A pragmatic doer, detribilised manager of men and indeed hands on leader. Tinubu will get Nigeria right. He commended President Buhari, the APC governors, all APC stakeholders and all APC delegates to the Presidential Convention for giving Tinubu to Nigeria as APC flag bearer adding “The time for Nigeria has arrived.”